725991f-a.text:
175th Street, east side, at the head of Douglas Avenue, showing old Jamaica homes, just south of the Long Island Railroad.

P. L. Sperr

April 1, 1932

727235f-a.text:
Liberty Avenue, north side, at 175th Street.  Several very old houses can be seen on both sides of 175th Street, formerly known as Larch Street.  In 1891 the property was owned by J. Day.  This part of Liberty Avenue was formerly South Street, one of the main east-west highways in this part of the county.

P. L. Sperr

April 1, 1932
